  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.crowdstrike.com/en-us/cybersecurity-101/threat-intelligence/open-source-intelligence-osint/&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Crowdstrike OSINT Article&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other interesting resources
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.akamai.com/glossary/what-is-a-cdn&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Content Delivery Network&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Passive Information Gathering Tools&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;passive-information-gathering-tools&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#passive-information-gathering-tools&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Domain Information
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/06_tools/06.1_web/whois/&#34;&gt;Whois&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lookup tool&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ICANN&amp;rsquo;s website&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subdomain Identification
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DNSDumpster&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certificate transparency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;crt.sh&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional Insights
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shodan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Service Discovery&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;service-discovery&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#service-discovery&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apart from the above mentioned, there are methods to discover running services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The most common toolkit used for that is &lt;code&gt;Nmap&lt;/code&gt;, that is used to discover open ports and services on a host or across entire networks.
